<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Ebadf on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/ebadf/</link><description>Recent content in Ebadf on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/ebadf/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] C Bad file descriptor: EBADF</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/bad-file-descriptor/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/bad-file-descriptor/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="bad-file-descriptor-ebadf"&gt;Bad file descriptor: EBADF&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;EBADF occurs when you use a file descriptor that is not valid. This can happen when the descriptor was never opened, was already closed, or is not open for the requested operation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: Using closed file descriptor
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; fd &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;open&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;file.txt&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, O_RDONLY);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;close&lt;/span&gt;(fd);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;read&lt;/span&gt;(fd, buf, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;100&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// EBADF
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Wrong descriptor for operation
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; fd &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;open&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;file.txt&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, O_RDONLY);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;write&lt;/span&gt;(fd, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;data&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;4&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// EBADF — fd is read-only
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Using uninitialized fd
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; fd;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;read&lt;/span&gt;(fd, buf, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;100&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// EBADF — fd is garbage
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-check-fd-validity"&gt;Fix 1: Check fd validity&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; fd &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;open&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;file.txt&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, O_RDONLY);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (fd &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;==&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;perror&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;open&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-dont-use-closed-descriptors"&gt;Fix 2: Don&amp;rsquo;t use closed descriptors&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; fd &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;open&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;file.txt&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, O_RDONLY);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// ... use fd ...
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;close&lt;/span&gt;(fd);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Don&amp;#39;t use fd after this
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-use-correct-open-flags"&gt;Fix 3: Use correct open flags&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// For writing
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; fd &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;open&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;file.txt&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, O_WRONLY &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; O_CREAT, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0644&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/too-many-open-files/"&gt;Too many open files&lt;/a&gt; — EMFILE.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/permission-denied-file/"&gt;Permission denied&lt;/a&gt; — EACCES.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/no-such-file/"&gt;No such file&lt;/a&gt; — ENOENT.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Node.js EBADF: bad file descriptor Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/javascript/ebadfd/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/javascript/ebadfd/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="nodejs-ebadf--bad-file-descriptor"&gt;Node.js EBADF — bad file descriptor&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This error occurs when attempting to read from, write to, or close a file descriptor that is invalid, already closed, or never existed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common error messages:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;Error: EBADF: bad file descriptor, read&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;Error: EBADF: bad file descriptor, write&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;Error: EBADF: bad file descriptor, close&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A file descriptor (fd) is a reference to an open file. After closing a file, its fd becomes invalid and cannot be used again.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Linux EBADF (errno 9) — Bad File Descriptor Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/errno-9/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/errno-9/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="linux-ebadf-errno-9--bad-file-descriptor"&gt;Linux EBADF (errno 9) — Bad File Descriptor&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;EBADF (errno 9) means you passed a file descriptor to a system call that is not valid. The descriptor may have never been opened, already been closed, or never existed at all. This error appears with calls like &lt;code&gt;read()&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;write()&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;close()&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;dup()&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;fcntl()&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;ioctl()&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;mmap()&lt;/code&gt;, and &lt;code&gt;send()&lt;/code&gt;/&lt;code&gt;recv()&lt;/code&gt;. It often signals a bug in resource management within your code.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Closing a file descriptor twice (double-close bug)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using a file descriptor after calling &lt;code&gt;close()&lt;/code&gt; on it&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passing -1 or an uninitialized variable as a file descriptor&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attempting to read/write on a descriptor that was never successfully opened&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A failed &lt;code&gt;open()&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;socket()&lt;/code&gt;, or &lt;code&gt;pipe()&lt;/code&gt; was not checked before use&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;File descriptor table overflow causing &lt;code&gt;open()&lt;/code&gt; to return -1&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix-ebadf"&gt;How to Fix EBADF&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="1-check-return-values-before-using-file-descriptors"&gt;1. Check Return Values Before Using File Descriptors&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Always verify that &lt;code&gt;open()&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;socket()&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;pipe()&lt;/code&gt;, or &lt;code&gt;dup()&lt;/code&gt; succeeded:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>